Dear Caniff Families,

We have had some delays with shipments and updating but, we are working very hard on our end to get devices out to all our families. Thank you for your patience with that.

DEVICES: If you still in need of a device, we are waiting on a few updates on our end. As soon as they are ready, we will post that info right here.

EMAIL: Students who had an email last year, will use the same email address this year to log into their lessons. You should be familiar with the process. If you have any issue with an email or your device, you may visit our Caniff Weebly page www.caniff2020.weebly.com and complete a Tech Help Ticket.

If you are a new student, or a student who is checking out a device for the first time, we will get your emails to you soon.

Look for all updates on Class Dojo and Facebook.

Again, we thank you for your patience.

post_text:
Today's world of education is very data driven. Every school uses data to help shape their teaching, curriculum, and to discover the best ways to help their students.

At Caniff Liberty Academy, like other schools, we are data driven to help our students. However, we believe that we must go beyond the data to truly help young people reach their full potential. When we look at our students, we don't just see data and test scores...We see a developing child. We see great potential. We see big dreams.

If you are looking for a school that goes beyond the data and test scores and truly sees your student, then perhaps Caniff Liberty Academy is the place for you and your student.

Now enrolling for the 2020-21 school year. Please click the link below, fill it out, and submit.

https://form.jotform.com/200985236619058

For more questions about our school or a paper enrollment form, please call our main office at 313-872-2000.

Your student' future...is our goal!

At Caniff Liberty Academy, like other schools, we are data driven to help our students. However, we believe that we must go beyond the data to truly help young people reach their full potential. post_text:
As we head toward the end of the school year, we believe it is important to continue to help support our current and potential future families and students.

One way that we want to do this is by providing helpful learning tips that can be done at home to keep students sharp educationally. We will provide these each week for different grade levels and ages.

This weeks tip is something that can be fun and done at any level.

Tip #1: Find a fun game that makes you think.

Examples: Connect Four, Chess, Scrabble, Trivial Pursuit, Checkers...the list could go on and on.

Enjoy the weekend and maybe find a fun game for the whole family. My son and I will be playing Connect Four. Its his new favorite game.

- Mr. Henwood, Principal
Caniff Liberty Academy

How do you measure success?

At Caniff Liberty Academy, we measure success by helping our students to grow academically. Don't just take our word for it...We were just honored in March as the number one most improved school in Michigan by the Mackinac Center of Public Policy. We are proud of this accomplishment, but we will never be fully satisfied. Our goal is to continue to get better and better. So if you are looking for a school that will challenge your student academically to reach their full potential, then Caniff Liberty Academy should be your new school home.

post_text:
Today's world of education is very data driven. Every school uses data to help shape their teaching, curriculum, and to discover the best ways to help their students.

At Caniff Liberty Academy, like other schools, we are data driven to help our students. However, we believe that we must go beyond the data to truly help young people reach their full potential. When we look at our students, we don't just see data and test scores...We see a developing child. We see great potential. We see big dreams.

If you are looking for a school that goes beyond the data and test scores and truly sees your student, then perhaps Caniff Liberty Academy is the place for you and your student.

Now enrolling for the 2020-21 school year. Please click the link below, fill it out, and submit.

https://form.jotform.com/200985236619058

For more questions about our school or a paper enrollment form, please call our main office at 313-872-2000.

Your student' future...is our goal!

This week we are focusing on getting new materials for grades Kindergarten to 5th grade. In order to practice safe social distancing, we will focus on a different grade each day. Families can come to the school to pick up their student's materials from 9 am to 2:30 pm. The schedule will be:

Tuesday - 1st grade
Wednesday - 2nd and 3rd grade
Thursday - 4th grade
Friday - 5th grade

After 2:30, our buses will look to deliver packets that didn't get picked up that day.

Tomorrow, Tuesday, we will be focusing on 1st grade students.

If you have questions, contact the main office or your student's teacher.

post_text:
Recently, I heard a quote from Viktor Frankl. The quote was:

"Everything can be taken from a man but one thing: the last of human freedoms - to choose one's attitude in any given set of circumstances, to choose one's own way."

As a history major, I had to learn more about Viktor and find out what his story was all about. Once I learned his story, the quote even became more powerful considering the current circumstances going on in the world.

Your assignment: Look up Viktor Frankl and find out why this quote is so powerful and fitting for our current situation with the coronavirus. - Mr. Henwood

post_text:
Caniff Liberty Families:

As you may know, Governor Whitmer announced that school buildings are not to be opened this year for face to face teaching. However, at the same time, she has encouraged us (educators and students) to keep learning.

Caniff Liberty Academy will continue to provide education for our students. This coming week, the staff is working hard preparing to get more educational materials for the students to go out the week of April 13. At the same time, please make sure your student is connected to their teacher through Class Dojo and/or email so that they can continue to get assignments.

We are also continuing to explore new ways to help educate our students off-campus. Please stay tuned for more updates to come.

We are in this together because your student's future...is our goal.

#CLAmissionpossible

post_text:
Caniff Liberty Students:

Today, I was checking out the school building. As I walked through the halls and checked the classrooms, I was taken back by how quiet it was. A school building just isn't the same without the students and staff. On behalf of the CLA staff, I wanted to let all of you know that we miss your smiling faces.

However, remember...we do not need a building to stay connected and keep teaching and learning. Education conquers all obstacles...when we work together.

- Mr. Henwood

#CLAmissionpossible

post_text:
Learning is a life long task. We must continue to seek opportunity even in challenging times. The Caniff Liberty Staff will continue to use all our resources to help our students to learn. Currently, teachers continue to reach out to students via Class Dojo, Youtube, Zoom, Google Classroom, Facebook, and more to communicate and teach lessons to their students. If you have not participated yet, the best place to start is by joining your teacher's Class Dojo or reaching out to them via email.

The state and federal leaders will make the decisions that they feel are best for us (The People). We are not always in control of those decisions. However, we can work together to continue to help our students grow and learn. Your student's future...is our goal.

A Story from my youth:

When I was a little Mr. Henwood, I always got up every Saturday morning and could not wait to watch Saturday morning cartoons...we didn't have the cartoon networks back then. During the cartoons, one of my all time favorite mini-cartoons was shown, called School House Rock. These cartoons provided fun little lessons through songs that helped my generation to learn all kinds of information. Today, I want to share with you one of my all time favorite School House Rocks...I'm just a bill. Enjoy. - Mr. Henwood

post_text:
March 13, 2020

Dear Parent/Guardian:
Per the Governor's directive last night, Caniff Liberty Academy will be closed for students beginning Monday, March 16. We will stay closed until April 6, pending further notice from the Governor, the Michigan Department of Education, and the Wayne County Health Department.

We will be sending another letter on Monday, March 16 about how we can keep your child connected with academics and continue learning with Caniff Liberty Academy. Our building will be open from 10:00 am-3:00 pm, Monday-Thursday, for parents only so that we can make printed materials available.

More information regarding State provided meals plans will become available when we get briefed. Thank you for your patience as we work through this unprecedented event.

Sincerely,

Scott Henwood, Principal
Caniff Liberty Academy

Administration is meeting this morning and working on a plan for our school. We will continue to keep you posted with updates.

post_text:
Caniff Liberty Academy celebrates Black History Month:

Madam C. J. Walker, was an American entrepreneur, philanthropist, and a political and social activist. Walker was considered the wealthiest African-American business woman and wealthiest self-made woman in America at the time of her death in 1919.
Walker made her fortune by developing and marketing a line of cosmetics and hair care products for black women through the business she founded, Madam C. J. Walker Manufacturing Company. Born in a village in Louisiana, she moved North to develop her business.

post_text:
Caniff Liberty Families - You are invited to our Back to School Night on September 11th from 4:30 pm to 6:30 pm.

This is an opportunity to meet your student's teacher and our leadership team. Furthermore, you can check out some of the updates that were made to the school over the Summer.

Hope to see you there.

post_text:
Caniff Families - Thank you for your support today, the first day of school.

Remember breakfast is served at 8:20 am, and school starts at 8:45 am. Tomorrow is a full day so students get out at 3:45 pm.

To keep traffic moving in the morning and afternoon, it is important for parents to drop-off and to pick-up at the main entrance. Our staff will help guide your student to the cafeteria and their teacher in the morning and to the main entrance for pick-up in the afternoon. Thank you for your help.

Let's have a great year!

post_text:
Caniff Families:

Reminder the first day of school is Tuesday, August 27th. School starts at 8:45 am. Breakfast will be served from 8:20 to 8:40.

We will be having a Welcome Back Assembly first thing in the morning, at that time we will escort students to their assigned grade level teacher.

We will be on an early dismissal schedule for the first day, which will end at 1:45 pm.

It is going to be a great year!
